owski, W.S., In situ methane concentrations at Hydrate Ridge offshore Oregon: New constraints on the global gas hydrate inventory from an active margin (2003) Geology, 31, pp. 833-836. , and The ODP leg 204 scientific party; Milkov, A.V., Global estimates of hydrate-bound gas in marine sediments: How much is really out there? (2004) Earth Sci. Rev, 66, pp. 183-197; Van Dover, C.L., Blake Ridge methane seeps: Characterization of a soft-sediment, chemosynthetically based ecosystem (2003) Deep-Sea Res. I, 50, pp. 281-300; Markl, R.G., Bryan, G.M., Ewing, J.I., Structure of the Blake-Bahama outer ridge (1970) J. Geophys. Res, 75, pp. 4539-4555; Paull, C.K., Ussler III, W., Borowski, W.S., Speiss, F.N., Methane-rich plumes on the Carolina continental rise: Associations with gas hydrates (1995) Geology, 23, pp. 89-92; Wefer, G., Heinze, P.-M., Berger, W.H., Clues to ancient methane release (1994) Nature, 369, p. 282; Sen Gupta, B.K., Platon, E., Bernhard, J.M., Aharon, P., Foraminiferal colonization of hydrocarbon-seep bacterial mats and underlying sediment, Gulf of Mexico slope (1997) J. Foraminiferal Res, 27, pp. 292-300; Stakes, D.S., Orange, D., Paduan, J.B., Salamy, K.A., Maher, N., Cold-seeps and authentic carbonate formation in Monterey Bay, California (1999) Mar. Geol, 159, pp. 93-109; Rathburn, A.E., Levin, L.A., Held, Z., Lohmann, K.C., Benthic foraminifera associated with cold methane seeps on the northern California margin: Ecology and stable isotopic composition (2000) Mar. Micropaleontol, 38, pp. 247-266; Hill, T.M., Kennett, J.P., Spero, H.J., Foraminifera as indicators of methane-rich environments: A study of modern methane seeps in Santa Barbara Channel, California (2003) Mar. Micropaleontol, 49, pp. 123-138; Hill, T.M., Kennett, J.P., Valentine, D.L., Isotopic evidence for the incorporation of methane-derived carbon into foraminifera from modern methane seeps, Hydrate Ridge, Northeast Pacific (2004) Geochim. Cosmochim. Acta, 68, pp. 4619-4627; Barbieri, 